    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-21T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-21T06:00:00-05:00" n="133"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d133">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/2118: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-21T20:00:00+09:00"
                            >May 21, 1941—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 21—9:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>718. A highly placed Japanese informs me that a message was recently sent to
                    Baron Hiranuma by several prominent Japanese of high rank that if a crisis
                    should occur in Japanese foreign relations (obviously with the United States) he
                    must immediately bring about the fall of the Cabinet. My informant says that he
                    himself was asked to deliver the message but, as his own personal relations with
                    Hiranuma are not good, another messenger was chosen. Informant states that not
                    only the majority in the Cabinet but probably 90% of the intelligentsia in Japan
                    wish to avoid trouble with the United States and the implication was clearly
                    conveyed that they fear and are opposed to the policy of Matsuoka.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
